1. I loaded the AnimationPlayer node as a property using `onready` keyword.
2. I created a simple condition to play "walk" or "idle" animations based on the move_input length.
3. I added a character rotation based on the move_input vector using the `short_angle_to` helper function.
4. I changed the `move_and_slide` function to `move_and_slide_with_snap` to handle the slopes.

Remember to adapt the AnimationPlayer and animation names to match your project setup. If you have more animations, you can add more conditions and a state machine to manage them.

